<subSubSection id="7E83FE90F86DFF82FF3788907218FDF8" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF86DFF82FF3788907019FD85" blockId="9.[189,342,507,533]" box="[189,342,507,533]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading id="6D6E1A77F86DFF82FF3788907019FD85" bold="true" box="[189,342,507,533]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FF3788907019FD85" bold="true" box="[189,342,507,533]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF86DFF82FF378B407218FDF8" blockId="9.[186,1398,554,617]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Known from 
<collectingCountry id="4E8EED8BF86DFF82FEDC8B417086FDD4" box="[342,457,554,580]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, southwestern and northern 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FC838B41720AFDD4" baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[777,837,554,580]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
to Fukien Prov. of 
<collectingCountry id="4E8EED8BF86DFF82FB918B41752BFDD4" box="[1051,1124,554,580]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4E8EED8BF86DFF82FBE78B4175BBFDD4" box="[1133,1268,554,580]" name="Philippines" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="4E8EED8BF86DFF82FB778B41743DFDD4" box="[1277,1394,554,580]" name="Indonesia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, New 
<collectingCountry id="4E8EED8BF86DFF82FF738B25701EFDF8" box="[249,337,590,616]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry id="4E8EED8BF86DFF82FE338B257331FDF8" box="[441,638,590,616]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5208D0EAF86DFF82FD078B257204FDF8" author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[653,843,590,616]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Stonedahl 1988</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7E83FE90F86DFF82FF378BFB728EFC5B" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF86DFF82FF378BFB7060FD3A" blockId="9.[189,303,656,682]" box="[189,303,656,682]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading id="6D6E1A77F86DFF82FF378BFB7060FD3A" bold="true" box="[189,303,656,682]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FF378BFB7060FD3A" bold="true" box="[189,303,656,682]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF86DFF82FF378BD5725EFC1A" blockId="9.[188,1401,702,906]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
This genus was revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="5208D0EAF86DFF82FD8F8BD5739CFD49" author="Stonedahl G. M." box="[517,723,702,729]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 99" refId="ref23015" refString="Stonedahl G. M. 1988. Revisions of Dioclerus, Harpedona, Mertila, Myiocapsus, Prodromus and Thaumastomiris (Heteroptera: Miridae, Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 187: 1 - 99." type="journal article" year="1988">Stonedahl (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and, with addition of the recently described 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FB798BD573C8FD6C" authority="Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016" authorityName="Yasunaga" authorityYear="2016" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stonedahli">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FB798BD57078FD6C" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Harpedona stonedahli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5208D0EAF86DFF82FEB78B8973C8FD6C" author="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T." box="[317,647,738,764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="411 - 469" refId="ref23196" refString="Yasunaga Y. &amp; Ishikawa T. 2016. Twelve new species of the Asian plant bug genus Ernestinus Distant (Heteroptera: Miridae: Bryocorinae: Eccritotarsini), with emphasis on unique biology and descriptions of three additional new eccritotarsine species. Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution 47 (5): 411 - 469. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 1876312 X- 47052149" type="journal article" year="2016">Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it currently comprises 13 species. Only 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FBD78B897010FC8F" authority="Distant, 1909" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguinipes">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FBD78B89743AFD6C" box="[1117,1397,738,764]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Harpedona sanguinipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5208D0EAF86DFF82FF368A6E7010FC8F" author="Distant W. L." box="[188,351,773,799]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="440 - 454" refId="ref21497" refString="Distant W. L. 1909. Descriptions of Oriental Capsidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 8 (4): 440 - 454. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930908692696" type="journal article" year="1909">Distant, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was known from 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FDC98A6E7330FC8F" baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[579,639,773,799]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
prior to our study; the description of a new species from the 
<collectingRegion id="F45D63F9F86DFF82FF378A427037FCD3" box="[189,376,809,835]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Karnataka state</collectingRegion>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FE238A4270AAFCD3" baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[425,485,809,835]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
is given below. 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FD338A427538FCD3" authority="Distant, 1904" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" box="[697,1143,809,835]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginata">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FD338A42728BFCD3" box="[697,964,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Harpedona marginata</emphasis>
Distant, 1904
</taxonomicName>
, the most frequently collected and widely distributed species of the genus was originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="4E8EED8BF86DFF82FB1D8A277445FCF6" box="[1175,1290,844,870]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and may likely be found in 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FE1E8A1B709FFC1A" baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[404,464,880,906]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
with more sampling effort.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF86DFF82FF378ADA728EFC5B" blockId="9.[189,961,945,972]" box="[189,961,945,972]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading id="6D6E1A77F86DFF82FF378ADA728EFC5B" bold="true" box="[189,961,945,972]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="3">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FF378ADA728EFC5B" bold="true" box="[189,961,945,972]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Key to species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FD988ADA73D4FC5C" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1904" box="[530,667,945,972]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FD988ADA73D4FC5C" bold="true" box="[530,667,945,972]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Harpedona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FD488ADA724AFC5B" baseAuthorityName="Poppius" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[706,773,945,971]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="India" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">India</taxonomicName>
and 
<collectingCountry id="4E8EED8BF86DFF82FCC88ADA728EFC5B" box="[834,961,945,971]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7E83FE90F86DFF82FF378A8B7438FB7D" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="key">
<key id="4208FA2AF86DFF82FF378A8B7438FB7D" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<keyStep id="8D6DB5BEF86DFF82FF378A8B7438FB8E" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF86DFF82FF378A8B7438FC6B" blockId="9.[189,1399,991,1054]" box="[189,1399,991,1019]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<keyLead id="8D680E2EF86DFF82FF378A8B7438FC6B" box="[189,1399,991,1019]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
1. Pronotum dirty orange, with distinct punctures (
<figureCitation id="AEA2B19EF86DFF82FC948A8B7235FC6A" box="[798,890,992,1018]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="43.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[255,1348,414,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-12@43.[189,1398,376,1856]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Fig. 2. Habitus of Ernestinus, Harpedona and Lopidolon spp. A. Ernestinus mimicus Distant, 1911, ♂, UASB. B. Ernestinus ramkeshariae Yasunaga &amp; Ishikawa, 2016, ♂, UASB. C. Harpedona sanguinipes Distant, 1904, ♂, UASB. D. Harpedona vittlaensis sp. nov, ♀, UASB. E–F. Lopidolon dandeliensis sp. nov., UASB. E. ♂. F. ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690366/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) ................................ 
<taxonomicName id="F199D698F86DFF82FBFD8A8B745AFC6A" authority="Yeshwanth &amp; Konstantinov, 2021" authorityName="Yeshwanth &amp; Konstantinov" authorityYear="2021" box="[1143,1301,991,1018]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Harpedona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittlaensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FBFD8A8B745AFC6A" bold="true" box="[1143,1301,991,1018]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">H. vittlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1FDECC72F86DFF82FA968A8A7438FC6B" box="[1308,1399,993,1019]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3626AD1BF86DFF82FF4B8D6F7438FB8E" blockId="9.[189,1399,991,1054]" box="[193,1399,1027,1054]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<keyLead id="8D680E2EF86DFF82FF4B8D6F7438FB8E" box="[193,1399,1027,1054]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="04ED7109F86DFF82FF4B8D6F719FFB8D" box="[193,208,1028,1053]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">–</emphasis>
Pronotum dark brown, smooth or very faintly punctate (
